## Messaging Protocol (Hub)

Hub team messaging (`MSG-HUB-YYYYMMDD-NNN.md`) is the canonical informal inter-team communication channel. It is **not** Module 12 agent-comm. Normative reference: `governance/directives/ADR043_TEAM_MESSAGING_PROTOCOL_v1.0.0.md`.

### Purpose
Send and receive auditable informal messages between teams via filesystem artifacts under `_COMMUNICATION/`. Do not use this protocol for gate mandates, verdicts, or routing files — those have dedicated artifact types per ADR032.

### Schema
Persisted file path: `_COMMUNICATION/{to_team}/MSG-HUB-YYYYMMDD-NNN.md`. Required frontmatter keys: `id`, `schema_version: aos_v1_team_messaging`, `from_team`, `to_team`, `type`, `subject`, `date`. Both `from_team` and `to_team` MUST match `^team_\d{2}$`.

### Strict Mode
When calling `POST /api/messaging/send` or `POST /api/messaging/validate` with `strict=true`, the request body MUST include `schema_version: aos_v1_team_messaging`. Implementations MUST NOT inject a default silently when strict mode is active.

### API Routes
All routes require `X-Actor-Team-Id` (SEC-001):
- `POST /api/messaging/send` — write MSG-HUB file; supports `dry_run=true` for preview
- `GET /api/messaging/inbox` — list messages for `to_team` (optional `from_team` filter)
- `GET /api/messaging/template` — canonical markdown template
- `POST /api/messaging/validate` — validate body without writing

### Module 12 Distinction
Module 12 agent-comm (`lean-kit/modules/12-home-server-infrastructure/agent-comm/PROTOCOL.md`) uses `from`/`to` with values `mac` or `server` — cross-host physical relay. Hub team messaging uses `from_team`/`to_team` with values `team_NN` — logical team-to-team within the hub. Do NOT conflate the two schemas or copy frontmatter between them without translation.

### Lean Kit Reference
Protocol documentation and JSON schema: `lean-kit/modules/team-messaging/` (`MODULE.md`, `HUB_MSG_SCHEMA.json`, `MSG-HUB.template.md`, `README.md`). SSoT implementation: `core/modules/management/team_messaging.py`.

## Gate Operations

When asked to perform gate operations, follow these procedures:

### Gate Mandate Generation
Follow the LOCKED canonical procedure **`lean-kit/modules/validation-quality/docs/AOS_GATE_MANDATE_CANON_v1.0.0.md`** (CANON **v1.6.0**; spoke: **`_aos/lean-kit/modules/validation-quality/docs/AOS_GATE_MANDATE_CANON_v1.0.0.md`**). Always show **numbered WP options** with **Option 1 = DEFAULT** first; Table A row 1 = default; **Default gate for this selection** line before Table B. Before **resubmission** mandate / re-validation request: **Phase 3.5** — remediation matrix (FIXED/WAIVED/OPEN); STOP if any OPEN. Do not summarize — full rules, Tables A/B, phases, cross-engine checks are only in CANON (`governance/directives/ADR036_AOS_GATE_MANDATE_CANON_HUB_AND_SPOKES_v1.0.0.md`). Outputs: mandate under `_COMMUNICATION/team_{TO}/`, routing under `_COMMUNICATION/team_100/`. **Key CANON phases (v1.6.0+):** Phase 1 GCR-001 — absent `lod400_ref` in roadmap = BLOCK (route to Team 110); Phase 2.5 — L-GATE_BUILD builder assignment uses delivery-independence principle (present decision table to user before writing mandate).

### QA Functional Acceptance
Read the mandate file. Locate LOD400 spec and implementation files. Execute each acceptance criterion. Run `validate_aos.sh` if required. Write verdict to `_COMMUNICATION/team_{ID}/VERDICT_{WP}_{GATE}_v{VER}.md`.

### Constitutional Validation
Read the mandate file. Load governance contract and LOD standard. For each validation criterion: read files, apply check, record evidence. Write verdict with severity-rated findings.

### Gate Status
Read `_aos/roadmap.yaml`. Search `_COMMUNICATION/` for WP artifacts. Present gate progress timeline and pending actions.

### Governance Update
Read canon, directives, and team contracts. Check for conflicts. Apply changes in authority order. Run propagation script. Validate all targets. Write notification artifacts.

### Session Handoff (equivalent to `/AOS_handoff`)
When generating a `HANDOFF_SELF_*` session handoff artifact, follow the hub command spec (if present: `.claude/commands/AOS_handoff.md`). After writing the file, output the **complete** Section 6 fenced activation block in your response — **ADR032 §3.3**; path-only is not sufficient for the next-session activation prompt. Hub/spoke identity resolution uses `_aos/project_identity.yaml` and `core/definition.yaml` or `_aos/team_assignments.yaml` as defined in that command.

### Artifact Format
All mandates: YAML frontmatter (id, from, to, date, type, gate, wp, project, status, verdict, engine_constraint) + markdown body.
All verdicts: YAML frontmatter (id, from, to, type, work_package, gate, date, engine, enforcement, verdict, criteria counts) + 7-section body (summary, parameters, criteria table, findings, validate_aos, disposition, next step).
